<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900910-0116</DOCNO><DOCID>900910-0116.</DOCID><HL>   General Host's Loss Narrows</HL><DATE>09/10/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B9</SO><CO>   GH</CO><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)SPECIALTY RETAILERS (OTS)</IN><LP>   STAMFORD, Conn. -- General Host Corp. posted a narrowedloss of $528,000 in the fiscal second quarter ended Aug. 12,compared with a year-earlier loss of $2.9 million.   The year-ago quarter included a charge to earnings of $3.4million stemming from an agreement to settle lawsuits broughtagainst it concerning discontinued operations. Sales roseslightly in the quarter to $115.1 million from $112.4 a yearago.</LP><TEXT>   For the six months, the company had net of $5 million, or26 cents a share, compared with a year-ago loss of $1.3million, which included the charge. Sales rose to $279.9million from $275.2 million.   General Host operates a chain of lawn and garden productsspecialty retail stores.</TEXT></DOC>